A \in \mathbb{R}^{n \times n}
a > 0
\|\hat x\|_2^2
\hat x
A
 \hat x = {\rm arg} \max_{x \in R^n}\ x' \left( \frac{1}{a + \|x\|^2_2} A \right) x  
E \in \mathbb{R}^{p \times p}
A + E
\|E\|
| \|\hat x\|_2^2 - \|\hat y\|_2^2 |
E
 \hat y = {\rm arg} \max_{y \in R^n}\ y' \left( \frac{1}{a + \|y\|^2_2} (A+E) \right) y 
\lambda
x_{\lambda}
x' A x \leq \lambda \left\| x \right\|^2
 x' \left( \frac{1}{a + \left\| x \right\|_2^2} A \right) x \leq \frac{\lambda \left\| x \right\|^2}{a + \left\| x \right\|^2} < \lambda 
x = t x_{\lambda}
t \to \infty
